meta {
  name: Score Transaction By ID
  type: http
  seq: 5
}

post {
  url: http://localhost:8090/score/by-id
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "company_id": "00000000-a1c0-deb0-0000-000000000001",
    "transaction_id": 21349
  }
}

docs {
  Score an existing transaction by id. The Rust service fetches the transaction
  from the foundry DB (joining vendors and vendor_findings) and runs it through
  the trained model.

  Response (200):
  {
    "company_id": "uuid",
    "transaction_id": 21349,
    "fraud_score": 0.45,
    "predicted_label": "ok",
    "threshold": 0.5,
    "model_trained_at": "2026-04-11T22:30:00Z"
  }

  Response (404):
  - "no model for company" -> need to call POST /train/{company_id} first
  - "transaction not found" -> the id doesn't exist in this company

  This is the endpoint the foundry transaction insert hook should call. Pass
  the company_id and the freshly-inserted transaction_id, store the returned
  fraud_score on the transaction row.

  Threshold semantics:
  - fraud_score >= threshold -> predicted_label = "fraud"
  - fraud_score <  threshold -> predicted_label = "ok"

  The threshold defaults to 0.5 but can be tuned via the DETECTION_THRESHOLD env
  var on the Rust service. Lower threshold = more recall, more false alarms.
  Higher = more precision, more misses.
}